pageContext.claim: “Maxine. She's a beauty. I mean, she practically was telling people the other day to assault. … Her own party was talking about censure. Let's see where that goes.”
pageContext.analysis: No Democrats called for censuring Rep. Maxine Waters, although some Republicans did. Waters said at a Los Angeles rally: "If you see anybody from that [Trump] Cabinet in a restaurant, in a department store, at a gasoline station, you get out and you create a crowd and you push back on them, and you tell them they're not welcome anymore, anywhere."
